.TH "vfs_get_link" 9 "vfs_get_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_get_link \- get symlink body
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" vfs_get_link
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "struct delayed_call *done "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
dentry on which to get symbolic link
.IP "done" 12
caller needs to free returned data with this
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls security hook and i_op->\fBget_link\fP on the supplied inode.

It does not touch atime.  That's up to the caller if necessary.

Does not work on "special" symlinks like /proc/$$/fd/N
